Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:27.949 --> 00:30.250
[Man shouts in Russian]

00:38.381 --> 00:41.946
_

00:41.946 --> 00:44.340
_

00:44.365 --> 00:46.266
What'd he say?

00:46.300 --> 00:49.069
Happy hour on the lido deck at 1600.

00:49.136 --> 00:50.670
Is there a magic show?

00:51.213 --> 00:52.982
_

00:54.083 --> 00:57.338
_

00:57.821 --> 00:59.234
_

00:59.467 --> 01:00.866
_

01:00.866 --> 01:02.768
_

01:02.768 --> 01:04.040
_

01:19.867 --> 01:23.169
<i>[Symphonic music playing]</i>

01:29.644 --> 01:31.978
[Door closes]

01:32.013 --> 01:36.516
Uh, Ava, leave us now, please.

01:39.820 --> 01:43.823
Is my father with you? Dr. Tophet?

01:49.664 --> 01:51.665
No, he's not.

01:51.699 --> 01:54.301
But he's alive... And safe on my ship.

01:57.572 --> 01:59.706
He tried very hard to be here himself,

01:59.740 --> 02:02.008
and he wanted me to tell
you he loves you very much.

02:04.245 --> 02:06.646
Ava, hurry along now, please.

02:10.550 --> 02:12.385
- [Door opens]
- That voice...

02:12.420 --> 02:14.788
- [Door closes]
- You must recognize it.

02:14.855 --> 02:17.938
It was Kelly... who pulled
the wool over your eyes

02:17.938 --> 02:20.026
back in Cuba pretending so well

02:20.061 --> 02:22.395
to be British commanding Officer.

02:22.430 --> 02:23.897
Excellent liars, the whole family.

02:23.931 --> 02:27.000
- That's enough!
- Oh, see how she treats me?

02:27.034 --> 02:30.837
I could have killed her
or fed her to my crew.

02:30.871 --> 02:33.206
Instead, I lavish her with
the treasures of the world.

02:33.240 --> 02:37.243
My own executive officer Asmik
gave up his stateroom for her

02:37.278 --> 02:39.079
and her insolent daughter.

02:39.113 --> 02:42.082
But nothing is good enough. [Chuckles]

02:43.584 --> 02:46.019
[Clicks tongue] Where are my manners?

02:46.053 --> 02:47.420
Please, sit.

02:49.724 --> 02:52.559
[Inhales and exhales deeply]

02:55.896 --> 02:58.932
<i>♪♪</i>

03:03.904 --> 03:07.540
I'd like to treat you with
the respect your rank affords,

03:07.575 --> 03:10.243
but you are going to
have to meet me halfway.

03:12.680 --> 03:16.583
Now, tell me of Dr. Scott's
progress with the vaccine.

03:16.651 --> 03:18.118
She's close, right?

03:19.453 --> 03:21.755
My name is Thomas Chandler,

03:21.789 --> 03:23.823
Commander, United States Navy,

03:23.858 --> 03:28.094
serial number 4242022634.

03:28.162 --> 03:29.663
There is no need for that.

03:29.697 --> 03:31.731
The Geneva Convention
doesn't exist anymore.

03:31.766 --> 03:35.235
Hell, Geneva doesn't
exist anymore! [Laughs]

03:35.302 --> 03:37.971
Ah...

03:38.039 --> 03:40.140
Still won't talk?

03:40.174 --> 03:41.574
See, I told you.

03:41.609 --> 03:43.610
He would rather go it alone and die

03:43.644 --> 03:46.479
than share in the glory
of saving the world.

03:47.782 --> 03:51.951
Why else would you, the ship's captain,

03:51.986 --> 03:53.620
personally lead the mission

03:53.654 --> 03:56.189
to save some poor island girl?

03:56.223 --> 03:58.858
Like with all tragic heroes,

03:58.893 --> 04:02.962
your hubris brought about your downfall.

04:02.997 --> 04:05.865
What do you have to say to
that, Commander Chandler?

04:11.172 --> 04:14.641
My name is Thomas Chandler,

04:14.675 --> 04:17.077
Commander, United States Navy,

04:17.144 --> 04:22.215
serial number 4242022634.

04:23.918 --> 04:25.318
Man over radio: Cobra
1-5 on final approach.

04:25.386 --> 04:27.120
- Secure down and lock.
- Woman: Cobra 1-5...

04:27.188 --> 04:29.656
Helos have crisscrossed
100 square miles of ocean.

04:29.690 --> 04:31.091
No sign of him.

04:31.125 --> 04:33.059
I don't know what I'm hoping for...

04:33.094 --> 04:35.128
Whether they're still somehow out there

04:35.162 --> 04:37.530
fighting for their lives, or the
Russians did get them.

04:37.565 --> 04:39.866
- Any sign of the <i>Vyerni?</i>
- Sir, nothing on the SLQ-32.

04:39.900 --> 04:41.534
Zero electronic emissions.

04:41.569 --> 04:43.303
They're most likely radio silent.

04:43.337 --> 04:46.673
- Maybe. But they're close.
- How do you know?

04:46.707 --> 04:49.175
Because if they have the
C.O., they're gonna call,

04:49.210 --> 04:51.010
try to make a trade...

04:51.045 --> 04:55.648
Tex and the C.O. for
Dr. Scott and her work.

04:55.716 --> 04:57.817
Rachel: So what you can see here

04:57.852 --> 05:00.153
is the virus attaching to receptors

05:00.187 --> 05:01.988
in a healthy human cell.

05:02.022 --> 05:03.990
Once attached, it invades

05:04.024 --> 05:05.692
and completely destroys its host

05:05.760 --> 05:07.293
before moving on to the next cell.

05:07.328 --> 05:08.862
This is what happens

05:08.896 --> 05:11.364
to everyone in the world
who contracts the virus.

05:11.432 --> 05:14.734
And death comes quickly...

05:14.769 --> 05:16.636
As you have seen.

05:16.670 --> 05:18.071
Yes.

05:18.105 --> 05:20.640
- [Mouse clicks]
- Now, here, once again,

05:20.674 --> 05:23.676
the virus is on the attack, but this time,

05:23.711 --> 05:26.279
the receptors to which it
attaches are free-floating,

05:26.313 --> 05:28.381
not part of a healthy cell.

05:28.449 --> 05:30.717
So it simply flushes out the system

05:30.751 --> 05:33.419
without causing any infection.

05:33.454 --> 05:35.622
And that...

05:35.656 --> 05:37.323
Is you, Bertrise.

05:37.391 --> 05:39.092
Those are your receptors,

05:39.126 --> 05:41.694
which I have injected into
our primate friend over there.

05:41.729 --> 05:45.064
And if it can fool the virus inside him...

05:45.099 --> 05:46.766
You'll have a vaccine?

05:46.801 --> 05:50.036
[Distant beeping]

05:50.070 --> 05:53.039
I was always so sick as a kid.

05:53.107 --> 05:55.608
Everyone used to tease
me that I was pretending

05:55.676 --> 05:58.077
so I wouldn't have to go to school.

05:58.112 --> 05:59.779
And now here I am.

05:59.814 --> 06:01.614
Immune to the most
deadly virus in the world

06:01.649 --> 06:03.149
and possibly its savior.

06:04.852 --> 06:07.053
[Door opens]

06:10.424 --> 06:13.793
Uh, Bertrise, I would
like to introduce you to...

06:13.828 --> 06:15.361
Will Mason.

06:15.429 --> 06:18.431
He's the one who heard
your call on the radio.

06:22.837 --> 06:25.104
It's very nice to meet you.

06:25.139 --> 06:26.606
I'm so glad that you're all right.

06:26.640 --> 06:29.843
Thank you for helping to find me.

06:32.279 --> 06:34.881
Is there any word on...

06:34.915 --> 06:36.883
Captain Chandler or Tex?

06:36.917 --> 06:38.151
No, ma'am.

06:38.185 --> 06:40.453
But we'll get them back.

06:40.487 --> 06:41.955
Somehow.

06:47.962 --> 06:51.130
Sir, Admiral Ruskov on the H.F.

06:58.839 --> 07:01.474
- This is Commander Slattery.
- <i>Commander.</i>

07:01.508 --> 07:03.309
I won't waste time.

07:03.344 --> 07:05.178
Obviously, I want Dr. Scott.

07:05.212 --> 07:07.313
Anything short of her delivery,

07:07.348 --> 07:11.251
along with all relevant
samples and work, will result in

07:11.285 --> 07:13.987
<i>the death of your
captain and his companion.</i>

07:22.596 --> 07:25.131
Are you still there, sir?

07:25.165 --> 07:27.000
<i>Of course you are.</i>

07:27.067 --> 07:29.369
<i>You just don't know what to say.
I understand.</i>

07:29.436 --> 07:31.037
You've never been in command before.

07:34.675 --> 07:36.209
I need proof of life.

07:36.243 --> 07:38.278
Let me talk to my commanding officer.

07:38.312 --> 07:39.779
[Radio squawks]

07:39.847 --> 07:42.248
I'm here, X.O.

07:42.283 --> 07:44.317
You have 10 minutes to decide.

07:44.351 --> 07:47.820
- What guarantees can you give me?
- <i>Just one...</i>

07:47.855 --> 07:49.589
If you don't comply with my demands,

07:49.623 --> 07:53.426
I will not only torture and
kill your friends, I will

07:53.460 --> 07:56.562
<i>annihilate your ship
and every soul on boar.</i>

07:56.597 --> 07:59.666
I possess enough nuclear
warheads to boil the seas

07:59.700 --> 08:01.434
<i>in which you pathetically sail.</i>

08:01.468 --> 08:03.136
10 minutes.

08:03.170 --> 08:04.437
[Radio static]

08:07.408 --> 08:09.175
[Beep]

08:09.209 --> 08:11.210
Combat, this is the X.O.

08:11.245 --> 08:13.880
Tell me you got a bearing on that call.

08:31.369 --> 08:32.736
[Shudders]

08:34.371 --> 08:35.972
Oh...

08:36.039 --> 08:38.475
My God.

08:38.509 --> 08:40.043
[Laughs]

08:40.078 --> 08:42.179
[Breathes sharply, sniffles]

08:42.246 --> 08:45.048
- [Chittering]
- Well, aren't you the lucky one?

08:45.083 --> 08:47.284
[Laughing]

08:52.357 --> 08:53.991
Danny: We break 'em out,
soft-kill the engines,

08:54.025 --> 08:55.566
and haul ass to the extract point

08:55.566 --> 08:57.461
- at the back of the <i>Vyerni.</i>
- That ship's twice our size.

08:57.495 --> 08:59.496
If the alarms sound while
you're going door-to-door

08:59.531 --> 09:00.998
looking for the C.O.,
it's gonna be four of you

09:01.065 --> 09:03.300
- against 300 angry Russians.
- It's doable, sir.

09:03.334 --> 09:04.378
Who's team leader? You?

09:04.403 --> 09:05.903
I wouldn't volunteer
unless I were fit, sir.

09:05.904 --> 09:08.672
- [Door opens]
- Even at 80%, he's good to go, sir.

09:08.740 --> 09:10.440
Honestly, Doctor, now is not the time.

09:10.475 --> 09:12.042
The Russians are calling
back in less than five.

09:12.076 --> 09:13.677
I have the vaccine!

09:13.711 --> 09:16.580
[Breathing heavily]

09:16.614 --> 09:17.881
The monkey survived.

09:19.984 --> 09:21.251
The last damn monkey.

09:21.286 --> 09:23.554
Are you saying you have the vaccine?

09:25.623 --> 09:28.592
- A vaccine that works?
- Well, in an ideal world, I'd...

09:28.660 --> 09:31.595
Do more testing, but... Yes.

09:33.097 --> 09:34.698
Which means Ruskov doesn't need me anymore.

09:34.732 --> 09:36.200
You can send him a dose in exchange

09:36.234 --> 09:37.601
for Tex and the captain.

09:37.635 --> 09:39.436
Ruskov won't just take your word for it.

09:39.470 --> 09:42.105
He'll want to make sure.

09:42.173 --> 09:44.775
Well then I'll show him myself.

09:44.809 --> 09:47.144
I'm no longer essential on this ship.

09:47.178 --> 09:50.047
From here on in, it's merely a case of

09:50.081 --> 09:52.115
mass-producing the vaccine
from my original formula.

09:52.150 --> 09:52.707
But, Doctor...

09:52.732 --> 09:54.451
I can show doc Rios
everything he needs to know.

09:54.452 --> 09:57.154
And if extra help is
required, I'm sure you can

09:57.188 --> 09:58.822
strike a bargain with Quincy.

09:58.856 --> 10:00.224
I can't let you go.

10:00.291 --> 10:02.559
Ruskov asked for me.

10:02.594 --> 10:04.027
And I won't do a thing for him

10:04.062 --> 10:05.963
until he releases Tex and the captain.

10:05.997 --> 10:07.965
Danny: Ma'am, you don't realize
what you're signing up for.

10:07.999 --> 10:09.833
You would be Ruskov's slave for life,

10:09.867 --> 10:11.235
or until he decides to kill you.

10:11.269 --> 10:13.837
Look, we all know

10:13.871 --> 10:16.440
he'll chase us to the ends of the Earth.

10:17.675 --> 10:20.444
This is the only way to stop him

10:20.478 --> 10:22.246
once and for all.

10:27.845 --> 10:32.646
_

10:32.671 --> 10:36.162
_

10:36.187 --> 10:39.523
_

10:39.548 --> 10:40.701
_

10:40.726 --> 10:42.142
_

10:48.439 --> 10:50.274
[Door opens]

10:52.744 --> 10:54.044
[Shouts in Russian]

10:55.880 --> 10:57.147
[Key jangles]

11:00.318 --> 11:03.253
Coming forward now. Give to me hands.

11:03.288 --> 11:07.958
[Keys jangle, cuffs clicking]

11:11.929 --> 11:13.830
You've looked better. [Sighs]

11:13.865 --> 11:15.465
Oh, you should have seen the other guy.

11:15.500 --> 11:16.900
There was only one?

11:16.934 --> 11:19.002
He was a big unit.

11:19.070 --> 11:21.338
No sense of humor.

11:21.372 --> 11:23.307
You want to know the kicker?

11:23.341 --> 11:25.375
He didn't even ask me any questions.

11:25.443 --> 11:27.878
Hey! No talk,

11:27.912 --> 11:29.680
- or I kiss your ass!
- [Both scoff]

11:29.714 --> 11:31.181
You mean <i>kick my ass!</i>

11:31.215 --> 11:32.883
Just shut up your head, okay?

11:36.421 --> 11:39.556
[Lowered voice] I spoke
to our friend from Chicago.

11:39.590 --> 11:41.591
If I know Mike,

11:41.626 --> 11:44.161
he's planning on paying us a visit.

11:44.195 --> 11:45.562
[Lowered voice] We'd better find a way

11:45.596 --> 11:47.030
to make him feel welcome.

11:50.702 --> 11:53.537
<i>Kirov</i> class battleships
run on a C.O.N.A.S. system.

11:53.604 --> 11:56.239
That's combined nuclear
and steam propulsion.

11:56.274 --> 11:57.908
Not gonna be able to take out both boilers,

11:57.942 --> 12:00.777
so if you want to kill
her, gotta damage the shaft.

12:00.812 --> 12:03.213
Engines can spin all day,
but the props won't turn.

12:03.281 --> 12:05.015
Not gonna be able to burn through them

12:05.049 --> 12:07.050
with the incendiaries I'm carrying.

12:07.118 --> 12:08.952
There's a soft spot
you're gonna have to find.

12:08.986 --> 12:10.687
But you're gonna have to be careful, sir.

12:10.722 --> 12:12.322
There could be a meltdown if
you use too many explosives.

12:12.357 --> 12:14.124
Yeah, and we're all
dead and we lose the C.O.

12:14.158 --> 12:16.460
- Right.
- Which is why you're coming with.

12:18.830 --> 12:20.831
Like I said before, you're part of my team.

12:23.901 --> 12:25.435
You ready to bring it?

12:26.804 --> 12:28.171
Hell, yeah, sir.

12:29.474 --> 12:31.575
- [Pats back]
- Let's map this out.

12:31.642 --> 12:33.744
This is a .45 caliber pistol.

12:33.811 --> 12:35.579
Excellent knock-down
power, but the trade-off

12:35.646 --> 12:37.147
is that it's large and heavy.

12:37.181 --> 12:39.950
It's a got an 8-round magazine, loaded.

12:39.984 --> 12:42.085
And I'm gonna give you an extra.

12:42.120 --> 12:43.920
Let's hope you won't need it.

12:43.955 --> 12:45.555
And lastly, the suppressor.
It's highly effective.

12:45.590 --> 12:47.457
Without it, you'll wake up the entire ship.

12:47.525 --> 12:50.093
- But you need time to attach it.
- Are we clear?

12:50.128 --> 12:52.896
- Crystal.
- Outstanding.

13:05.009 --> 13:06.576
Thank you.

13:11.149 --> 13:14.084
If anything should happen...

13:14.118 --> 13:15.886
Finish what we started.

13:17.789 --> 13:20.991
[Door opens]

13:26.297 --> 13:28.598
The Russians are picking
you up in one of their helos

13:28.666 --> 13:30.834
out in the middle of nowhere,
taking you to their ship.

13:30.868 --> 13:32.235
We won't have any contact after that.

13:32.303 --> 13:34.171
- I understand.
- [Huffs]

13:35.540 --> 13:39.509
It's a little late to ask if
you really want to do this.

13:39.544 --> 13:41.178
Let me just say,

13:41.212 --> 13:45.182
what you're doing is... Very brave.

13:45.216 --> 13:46.650
I'm proud to know you.

13:48.319 --> 13:50.620
You're making it sound like good-bye.

13:52.256 --> 13:53.723
I'll see you for breakfast.

14:08.347 --> 14:10.743
[Lowered voice] How
about, uh, "Great Escape"?

14:10.743 --> 14:12.811
[Lowered voice] Kinda hard
to tunnel out of a ship.

14:12.845 --> 14:14.713
Yeah, you got a point there.

14:14.781 --> 14:16.815
You ever see "Papillon"?

14:16.849 --> 14:18.383
Are we just doing Steve McQueen flicks?

14:18.451 --> 14:19.618
What about "Escape from Alcatraz"?

14:19.652 --> 14:21.286
You'd need a dummy.

14:21.354 --> 14:23.855
What about, uh, Bad English over there?

14:23.923 --> 14:26.291
What are you talking of?! Quiet!

14:48.181 --> 14:49.448
Take off.

15:03.663 --> 15:05.163
Turn around.

15:15.475 --> 15:16.675
Good.

15:19.545 --> 15:22.047
[Speaks Russian]

15:22.081 --> 15:23.882
Virus samples.

15:34.360 --> 15:37.529
[Latches click]

15:47.707 --> 15:49.274
Okay, careful.

15:54.280 --> 15:56.214
[Latches click]

15:56.249 --> 15:57.516
Come.

16:05.458 --> 16:07.025
[Monitor beeps]

16:07.059 --> 16:09.060
Tracking device moving
at a steady 15 knots, sir.

16:09.095 --> 16:10.729
Looks like we're aboard the <i>Vyerni.</i>

16:10.763 --> 16:12.164
Extraction teams underway.

16:12.198 --> 16:14.633
We got you now, you son of a bitch.

16:14.700 --> 16:16.368
[Door opens]

16:21.908 --> 16:23.575
Dr. Scott.

16:23.643 --> 16:27.512
How long I've waited to
welcome you aboard <i>Vyerni.</i>

16:27.547 --> 16:30.148
I won't be talking further

16:30.216 --> 16:31.816
or doing any kind of work

16:31.884 --> 16:33.552
until you bring up your prisoners.

16:33.586 --> 16:35.720
Of course. It was expected.

16:41.761 --> 16:44.296
What the hell are you doing here?

16:46.232 --> 16:47.599
Huh?

16:50.069 --> 16:51.303
Ohh!

16:55.007 --> 16:56.608
Now I understand

16:56.642 --> 16:59.110
why the good Doctor
agreed to pay us a visit.

16:59.145 --> 17:01.746
- [Speaks Russian]
- [Grunts]

17:01.781 --> 17:03.582
- [Door opens]
- The deal was me for them.

17:03.616 --> 17:05.550
You gave your word that you'd let them go.

17:05.585 --> 17:07.319
Not until I confirm

17:07.353 --> 17:09.154
that you've delivered what I've requested.

17:10.455 --> 17:12.624
Well, I assume you have a lab.

17:22.167 --> 17:23.801
- [Equipment beeping]
- Ah.

17:23.836 --> 17:25.637
Dr. Scott.

17:27.339 --> 17:28.640
Ah.

17:30.843 --> 17:34.412
So nice to see you again.

17:34.447 --> 17:36.248
Do I know you?

17:36.282 --> 17:39.751
European Congress of Virology, 2011.

17:39.785 --> 17:43.355
Uh, you spoke on techniques
for hemagglutination-inhibition

17:43.389 --> 17:45.590
with arthropod-borne viruses.

17:45.625 --> 17:49.261
And afterwards, I introduced
myself, shook hands.

17:49.295 --> 17:51.196
Niels Sorensen.

17:51.230 --> 17:53.832
I'm sorry. I don't recall.

17:53.866 --> 17:56.201
I was with Professor Lindblom.

17:56.235 --> 17:57.836
I remember Jonas.

17:57.870 --> 17:59.671
You were in his department?

17:59.705 --> 18:01.973
Um... for a time.

18:02.008 --> 18:05.477
Uh, he... never really saw clearly

18:05.511 --> 18:09.948
what I was trying to, uh...

18:09.982 --> 18:13.084
Anyways...

18:13.152 --> 18:15.086
I'd invite you in, but it's such a mess.

18:15.154 --> 18:17.155
[Laughs]

18:17.189 --> 18:20.759
Uh, actually, they are, uh,
supposed to clean up every day.

18:20.826 --> 18:24.529
And I tell them that the
U.V. light kills the virus,

18:24.563 --> 18:28.033
but, um... [Laughs]

18:28.067 --> 18:30.368
You're infected.

18:30.403 --> 18:31.970
Uh, not exactly.

18:32.004 --> 18:33.305
But you're not even symptomatic.

18:33.339 --> 18:34.706
Um...

18:34.740 --> 18:36.408
Perhaps I should explain.

18:36.442 --> 18:37.842
It was you.

18:37.877 --> 18:40.779
- You added the human gene.
- Yes.

18:42.081 --> 18:43.782
You weaponized the virus!

18:43.849 --> 18:45.317
What? No.

18:45.351 --> 18:46.651
No, I didn't weaponize it.

18:46.686 --> 18:50.322
I was really close to a major breakthrough.

18:50.356 --> 18:52.691
I added my gene to the virus

18:52.725 --> 18:54.859
and then injected it
back into my bloodstream,

18:54.894 --> 18:56.528
and it worked.

18:56.562 --> 18:59.798
I am completely immune. I just...

18:59.832 --> 19:03.134
Uh, I didn't know that I
also made myself a carrier.

19:03.169 --> 19:05.236
So you're patient zero?

19:05.271 --> 19:06.638
No, I didn't start it.

19:06.706 --> 19:08.840
I'm trying to find a solution here.

19:08.908 --> 19:10.709
I'm trying to fix it, and I can fix it

19:10.743 --> 19:12.777
as soon as I get the primordial strain.

19:12.812 --> 19:14.946
- If that...
- You don't understand what you've done.

19:14.980 --> 19:17.549
The primordial won't work now.

19:17.583 --> 19:19.384
The virus that you created,

19:19.418 --> 19:22.887
the modifications you made...
You've made it so much worse.

19:22.955 --> 19:25.890
And you could have come
forward at any point.

19:25.925 --> 19:27.559
I mean, you must have known this.

19:27.593 --> 19:29.361
No, that was too late.

19:29.395 --> 19:31.029
There was zero benefit from me
coming forward at that point...

19:31.063 --> 19:32.864
You killed four billion people.

19:32.898 --> 19:34.699
- I didn't...
- And you never gave them a chance

19:34.734 --> 19:36.901
- to understand how it happened?
- But I can now.

19:36.936 --> 19:39.504
- I mean, can solve it now.
- It's too late.

19:39.538 --> 19:41.106
I've already done it.

19:41.140 --> 19:42.707
[Scoffs]

19:42.742 --> 19:44.075
I already made the vaccine.

19:44.110 --> 19:46.444
- That's a lie!
- See for yourself.

19:46.479 --> 19:49.347
Hey, that... no. You're not
allowed to do that, actually.

19:49.382 --> 19:50.414
That's mine!

19:50.439 --> 19:51.950
I would like to speak
with the admiral, please.

19:51.951 --> 19:53.918
No! She doesn't go anywhere! Unh!

19:53.953 --> 19:55.587
You don't get to do it without me.

19:55.621 --> 19:57.389
Did you really think

19:57.423 --> 19:59.457
that your D.N.A. could save the Human race?

20:05.297 --> 20:07.298
Dr. Scott...

20:09.769 --> 20:11.269
[Door closes]

20:11.303 --> 20:12.971
[Handcuffs click]

20:13.038 --> 20:14.939
[Clattering]

20:14.974 --> 20:16.741
Unbelievable.

20:16.776 --> 20:20.412
I mean, I can't believe she kissed you.

20:20.446 --> 20:22.580
You're a married man, for Pete's sake.

20:22.615 --> 20:24.616
And you're Navy. Did you not get the talk?

20:24.650 --> 20:27.118
No fraternization with the ladies, buddy.

20:29.355 --> 20:31.689
[Breathes sharply]

20:36.829 --> 20:41.666
[Lowered voice] "Ladder
room. Port side, 0400."

20:41.734 --> 20:43.268
[Lowered voice] You know where that is?

20:43.302 --> 20:45.336
I have an idea.

20:45.404 --> 20:47.305
First we gotta get by this guy.

20:47.339 --> 20:49.474
And there's two guards on the P-Way.

20:49.508 --> 20:51.676
Goddamn it. He had to send her.

20:51.710 --> 20:53.511
Right? I mean, I'm standing right there.

20:53.546 --> 20:55.013
She could have easily passed me the note.

20:55.080 --> 20:56.648
Tex...

20:56.682 --> 20:58.683
0400.

20:58.751 --> 21:00.018
Got it.

21:13.847 --> 21:15.414
You lied to me!

21:15.448 --> 21:17.316
I took you in because you told me

21:17.350 --> 21:19.752
she was not capable of
succeeding without you.

21:19.819 --> 21:23.222
Now I find you've wasted
my time and resources.

21:23.289 --> 21:26.925
Do you really think I've kept
myself in here for nothing?

21:26.960 --> 21:30.329
I'm telling you, Admiral,
her vaccine won't work.

21:30.363 --> 21:31.864
You still need me.

21:31.898 --> 21:34.800
That's right. I do.

21:37.944 --> 21:40.455
_

21:40.455 --> 21:42.976
_

